25|$|Magnetic mirror: Developed by Richard F. Post {{and teams}} at LLNL in the 1960s. Magnetic mirrors {{reflected}} hot plasma {{back and forth}} in a line. Variations included the Tandem Mirror, <b>magnetic</b> <b>bottle</b> and the biconic cusp. A series of well-funded, large, mirror machines were built by the US government in the 1970s and 1980s, principally at Lawrence Livermore National Laboratory.|$|E
