5000|$|The {{design of}} a {{magnetic}} mirror machine {{was first published in}} 1967. [...] The concept was developed in the US by Richard F. Post and his team at Lawrence Livermore National Laboratory during the late sixties. [...] Partially due to the 1970s energy crisis and the Cold War the funding was available for a massive magnetic mirror and <b>magnetic</b> <b>bottle</b> research program. This led to a series of machines starting in the late 1960s and continuing into the mid eighties. This included the 2X <b>magnetic</b> <b>bottle</b> and Baseball I, Baseball II mirror machines before the TMX was built.|$|E
