5000|$|Taylor {{initiated}} {{the study of}} chaos in magnetic surfaces, developing several contributions to chaos theory and introducing the [...] "standard map" [...] (or Chirikov-Taylor map). He studied 2D-plasmas, demonstrating the inherent Bohm diffusion which had been noticed in <b>magnetic</b> <b>bottles</b> since the 1950s. He then played a major part in developing the [...] "ballooning transformation" [...] for toroidal plasmas, along with Jack Connor and Jim Hastie, which won the 2004 Hannes Alfvén Prize.|$|R
